c: 42
v: 48
t: "But if they turn away, We have not sent you Ë¹O ProphetËº as a keeper over them. Your duty is only to deliver Ë¹the messageËº. And indeed, when We let someone taste a mercy from Us, they become prideful Ë¹becauseËº of it. But when afflicted with evil because of what their hands have done, then one becomes totally ungrateful"